9:
Cheeks caress and flowers bloom,
I invoke thee, zephyr sweet.
13:
Hehe. You carry fluff, do you?
That must mean there are dandelions
around here.
22:
No! I did not mean to stop you!
I was merely impressed by your art.
26:
This... This place is full of wind sprites.
Every soft breeze and sudden gale is
led here by them.
28:
THEY'RE the magical ones...
I just give them form.
31:
Your gifts are also singular.
I am sorry I startled you.
I'll leave you be.
36:
I heard you were once a champion.
And even now, after you've lost your
powers, you haven't stopped fighting.
38:
Why? Why don't you run away?
Is it because war is your calling?
42:
If I thought war was my calling,
I'd have given up long ago.
48:
There is something I cannot cast
aside... A dream of mine.
50:
There is no war now I can win alone.
But dreams can be shared and passed
on. That thought alone has given me
the strength to carry on.
52: There was also a dream I shared in...
57:
No, Phiria. When you must be forced to
fight for it, that is no dreamâ€”
it is selfish ambition.
65:
Stella spoke to me. She said you are
haunted by nightmares.
Memories of war.
70:
I... Oh, I ran... I knew they had no hope
without me, but I still threw them
away...
77:
I didn't mean to do such a horrid thing.
But I... I was so frightened!
80:
I wanted to protect them!
I wanted to save her!
83: Finally... you realize your true desire.
89:
Phiria.
This time, defend your own dream.
91:
You need not harm anyone. Defend
your dream in what way seems
best to you.
97:
You can. As long as there is something
you wish to protect.
103: I wish to protect the wind.
111:
She... The wind sprite. She told me
she likes it here.
114:
I do too. The wind blows freely in
Starview. I want to see it go on forever...
Is that a silly dream?
117: No. It is one people can share in.
123:
Light, I wish to grow stronger. So I never
have to run away from what's dear to
me again...
